      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 612: The MediaRecorder info callback stops and releases the recorder immediately when the size/duration limit is reached, but the dialog still shows a Send button wired to stopAndSendAudioRecording(). Because audioRecorder is already null at that point, the send path skips recorder.stop() and sends whatever file exists. That can race with finalization and may send a partially finalized/corrupt MP4/AAC file. Prefer using the same stop-and-send path, or disable recording and only enable Send after recorder.stop() has completed on the UI thread.\n\n```suggestion\nsetOnInfoListener { _, what, _ -\u003e\n    if (what \u003d\u003d android.media.MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_DURATION_REACHED ||\n        what \u003d\u003d android.media.MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_FILESIZE_REACHED) {\n        requireActivity().runOnUiThread {\n            stopAndSendAudioRecording()\n            audioRecordDialog?.dismiss()\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
      "revId": "55526ce8f3205ed60e7579a2cf39c36fada44dc2",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
